Agent in UrbanCode Deploy (uDeploy)

An Agent is a lightweight program installed on a target system (like a server or VM) that executes deployment tasks sent by the uDeploy server.


---

Key Points:

Runs deployment steps like copying files, running scripts, restarting services.

Communicates securely with the uDeploy server.

Can be part of agent pools for load balancing and high availability.

Tied to resources, which are mapped to environments.



---

Think of an agent as a remote worker that does the hands-on job of deploying your app to a specific machine.

